Package: inteRn
Type: Package
Title: Helps calculate every day scores used in internal medicine
Version: 1.0
Date: 2021-11-04
Author: Carlos C Vera Recio
Maintainer: Carlos C Vera Recio <carlos.verarecio@gmail.com>
Description: This package is a compilation of the most frequently used scores and equations needed for PGY1 residents in Internal Medicine. A few examples are the CHADS-VASC score for need of anti-coagulation in a patient with A-Fib, the creatinine clearance to adjust medication doses for renal function and corrections for sodium (hyperglycemia), calcium (albumin) and QT interval (QTc).
License: GPL-2
